# Merit History (–ò—Å—Ç–æ—Ä–∏—è –∑–∞—Å–ª—É–≥)

## Data source

- **Full history (self):** `transactions` for the user‚Äôs **global** wallet (`GLOBAL_COMMUNITY_ID`) via `WalletService.getUserTransactions` ‚Üí `wallets.getTransactions` (authenticated user **only**; `userId` must resolve to caller).
- **Peer-only contexts:** `meritTransfer.getByCommunity` on community/project **merit-transfers** pages ‚Äî **no** merge with wallet lines (TR-5: single source per surface).
- **Other user‚Äôs profile:** `meritTransfer.getByUser` only ‚Äî **no** full wallet history (privacy).

## Categories

Map: `wallet-transaction-history.ts` (`MERIT_HISTORY_FILTER_KEYS`, `meritHistoryCategoryForReferenceType`, `meritHistoryReferenceTypeMatch`). Peer P2P in the global feed uses wallet lines with `referenceType === 'merit_transfer'` and `referenceId` = merit transfer record id (same id on sender debit and receiver credit ‚Äî **one logical transfer**, two ledger lines).

## Enrichment

`merit-history-enrichment.ts` batches publications, votes (including nested vote‚Üívote‚Üípublication), communities, polls, `merit_transfers`, and user display names. Exposed as `meritHistoryEnrichment` on each row from `wallets.getTransactions`. Safe fallbacks when documents are missing.

## UI routes

| Surface | Route | Feed |
|--------|-------|------|
| Own merit history | `/meriter/profile/merit-transfers` | `wallets.getTransactions` + filters |
| Context peer list | `/meriter/communities/[id]/merit-transfers`, `/meriter/projects/[id]/merit-transfers` | `meritTransfer.getByCommunity` |
| Other user | `/meriter/users/[id]/merit-transfers` | peer-only; own id redirects to profile hub |

